# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  PayGuard — environment config
#  ► Copy this file to ".env"   →   cp .env.example .env
#    (Use ".env", NOT ".env.local" — this project uses the `dotenv` package,
#     which loads ".env" by default.)
#  ► ".env" is git-ignored. NEVER commit real private keys.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Network — PRE-FILLED, no action needed ──────────────────────────────────
# Pharos Atlantic testnet. Source: docs.pharos.xyz/developer-guide/x402 + Chainlist (chain 688689).
RPC_URL=https://atlantic.dplabs-internal.com/
CHAIN_ID=688689

# ── Skill-to-Agent demo (OPTIONAL) ──────────────────────────────────────────
# `npm run agent` runs an autonomous Claude agent on a GuardianRail-guarded wallet.
# Without a key it runs a deterministic planner (fully offline, no key needed). Set
# this to drive it with a real Claude tool-use loop. Optionally pin a model.
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...
# ANTHROPIC_MODEL=claude-opus-4-8

# ── Wallets — FILL THESE ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Get a throwaway testnet key: `cast wallet new` (prints Address + Private key),
# or MetaMask → Account details → Show private key. (Testnet keys ONLY.)
#
# DECISION — should AGENT_PK and FACILITATOR_PK be the SAME or DIFFERENT key?
#   They are two ROLES, not necessarily two wallets:
#     • AGENT       = payer   → signs a GASLESS EIP-3009 authorization
#     • FACILITATOR = relayer → submits it on-chain and PAYS THE GAS
#
#   SAME key (paste one wallet's key in BOTH fields):
#     + simplest — fund only ONE wallet; fastest path to a green run
#     − the wallet effectively "pays itself" (less realistic)
#   DIFFERENT keys (two separate wallets):
#     + the REAL x402 model: a gasless agent + a gas-sponsoring facilitator
#     + stronger story for judges (demonstrates x402's whole value prop)
#     − must hold PHRS gas in BOTH wallets
#
#   >> RECOMMENDED: use the SAME key to confirm it works today, then switch
#      FACILITATOR_PK to a 2nd funded wallet for the submission demo recording.
#   >> RECEIVER_ADDRESS must ALWAYS differ from the agent (so you can see USDC move).

# AGENT — deploys MockUSDC (receives 1M test USDC) and signs the gasless EIP-3009
# payment. Needs a little PHRS only for the one-time MockUSDC deploy.
#   where: `cast wallet new`  → copy the "Private key" line here
AGENT_PK=0x...

# FACILITATOR — submits the on-chain settlement tx; MUST hold PHRS for gas.
#   where: `cast wallet new`  → then fund its ADDRESS from a Pharos faucet:
#     • https://testnet.pharosnetwork.xyz/            (official dashboard faucet)
#     • https://zan.top/faucet/pharos
#     • https://faucets.chain.link/pharos-atlantic-testnet
FACILITATOR_PK=0x...

# ── Addresses — FILL THESE ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
# USDC token (6 decimals, EIP-3009). Get it one of two ways:
#   • Deploy your own (recommended): from this folder run
#       forge script script/DeployMockUSDC.s.sol --rpc-url atlantic --broadcast
#     → console prints  "MockUSDC deployed at: 0x..."  ← paste that here
#   • Or the official Pharos testnet USDC, once confirmed in the Pharos Telegram/docs.
USDC_ADDRESS=0x...

# RECEIVER — where the 0.001 USDC payment lands. Use a SECOND address you control
# so you can watch the balance arrive in the demo.
#   where: `cast wallet address --private-key <a-key>`  or copy from MetaMask.
#   (For a quick probe only, the burn address 0x000...dEaD also works.)
RECEIVER_ADDRESS=0x...

# ── Optional ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Official Pharos x402 facilitator URL (ask in the Pharos Telegram). Leave BLANK
# to use PayGuard's self-hosted in-process facilitator (Hybrid / Option 3).
FACILITATOR_URL=

# Server port (server.ts) and the URL the demo client calls (demo.ts).
PORT=4021
SERVER_URL=http://localhost:4021
